Our goal is to work with families and their unique schedules to provide childcare for all of the children in their family. With longer hours and childcare for all of the children in their family, we provide childcare that fulfills all of the family's childcare needs. We strive to have an environment that is homey and private with a commercial appearance. With clean industry standard equipment and materials and staff members that welcome you and your children like you are family we hope to have children in our facility until their families no longer need childcare. Your child will try new things, increase in competence, and gain confidence as they grow and develop......Purposeful Environment: Our space is light-filled and inviting. The classroom is designed to encourage your child's independence, while facilitating and challenging their thinking. Carefully planned centers are provided for developmentally appropriate exploration......Cultivating Curiosity: We support children as inquisitive learners who are deeply curious and capable. Experiences are planned to spark creativity, thinking, and reflecting. Instructors develop emergent curriculum, responding to and encouraging the ever-changing interests of the students. This approach engages your child's sense of wonder about the world and their place within it......Building a Community: Social skill development is of utmost importance during the preschool years. Clear communication, listening and cooperation are modeled, encouraged and supported. Social skills developed during early childhood will sustain and enrich your child throughout their life and support them in developing heart-felt values, such as empathy and respect for one another......Partnering with Parents: We strive to establish strong connections and clear communication with parents in a number of ways including: a parent communication board at the preschool, twice annual parent teacher conferences, regular classroom blog posts, social events and parent workshops, as well as opportunities to include parents in the classroom.
